post_cb({"26900158": {"ViewCount": "56", "Body": "<pre><code>bool CWaypoint::less(CWaypoint const &amp;wp_right)\n{\n    bool result;\n    CWaypoint temp1;\n\n    (calculateDistance(temp1) &gt; temp1.calculateDistance(wp_right)) ?\n            result = 1 : result = 0;\n\n    return result;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>why don't I get an error even when I am not returning a bool type ?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "26900182", "Title": "function returning bool works even though it returns 1 or 0", "CreationDate": "2014-11-13T02:06:06.020", "Id": "26900158", "CommentCount": "5", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2014-11-13T02:08:33.487", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "4246363", "Tags": "<c++>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "26900182": {"Id": "26900182", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>An integer-to-boolean conversion takes place. From the C++ standard:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_26900158_26900182_0\"><strong>4.12 Boolean conversions [conv.bool]</strong></p>\n<p id=\"so_26900158_26900182_1\">A prvalue of arithmetic, unscoped enumeration, pointer, or pointer to member type can be converted to a\n  prvalue of type <strong>bool</strong>. A zero value, null pointer value, or null member pointer value is converted to <strong>false</strong>;\n  any other value is converted to <strong>true</strong>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2014-11-13T02:08:33.487", "CommentCount": "3", "CreationDate": "2014-11-13T02:08:33.487", "ParentId": "26900158", "Score": "6", "OwnerUserId": "3246555"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_26900158_26900182_1": {"length": 28, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 44}}, "n3337": {"so_26900158_26900182_1": {"length": 28, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 41}}, "n4659": {"so_26900158_26900182_1": {"length": 28, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 45}}}});